Yunnan: co-ordinate and standardize the management of rural public welfare positions - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Kunming, Dec. 12 (Xinhua Lin Bifeng) in order to continue to do a good job to help the employment of the population out of poverty, consolidate and expand the results of poverty alleviation, Yunnan Province recently introduced to promote rural revitalization of rural public welfare positions management-related policies, to help promote the overall revitalization of the countryside. The person in charge of the Yunnan Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security introduced that at present, Yunnan has developed 448,300 rural public welfare jobs for the placement of rural disadvantaged groups such as labor force out of poverty, which play an important role in helping people out of poverty to realize employment and increase income, consolidate the results of poverty eradication and effectively enhance the capacity of various public services in the countryside. The new rules are jointly issued by seven departments of Yunnan Human Resources, Rural Revitalization and Finance, mainly for the recruitment of grass-roots rural public service positions in the scope of the object, fund management, job development, job management and other aspects of unified norms. In terms of job development and setting, the new rules clearly state that in accordance with the principle of "setting posts according to needs, determining people with posts, dynamic management, total control", "who develops, who uses, who is responsible" and "one person one post, voluntary and open, unified management "the principle of setting. Recruitment procedures must be in accordance with the announcement, declaration, review, public announcement, employment, pre-service training and arrangements for induction and other steps. In addition, the new regulations also clarify the specific responsibilities of the main development departments of rural public service positions, rural public service positions subsidy standards and subsidies, and stipulate that the development departments of rural public service positions should purchase accidental injury commercial insurance for rural public service positions; require the relevant departments to regularly monitor the issuance of rural public service positions subsidies.
